{
  "video_id": "MSkeNmz7v4M",
  "title": "Pixar: The Story Behind the Studio",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 258.0,
      "end_time": 1412.0,
      "text": "(gentle music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 1412.0,
      "end_time": 3566.0,
      "text": "- [Voiceover] Most of us know Pixar as the established"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 3567.0,
      "end_time": 6101.0,
      "text": "dominating animation studio that it is today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 6101.0,
      "end_time": 7434.0,
      "text": "responsible for some of the greatest"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 7434.0,
      "end_time": 9334.0,
      "text": "animated movies of our time."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 9334.0,
      "end_time": 12170.0,
      "text": "But the truth is that this massively successful studio"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 12170.0,
      "end_time": 14199.0,
      "text": "came from a very humble beginnings."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 14199.0,
      "end_time": 15847.0,
      "text": "In fact, on it's first few years"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 15847.0,
      "end_time": 18396.0,
      "text": "the studio was constantly on the verge of bankruptcy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 18396.0,
      "end_time": 19811.0,
      "text": "losing millions of dollars"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 19811.0,
      "end_time": 22600.0,
      "text": "even after the success of Toy Story."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 22600.0,
      "end_time": 24580.0,
      "text": "In this video I'll tell you the story behind Pixar"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 24580.0,
      "end_time": 26711.0,
      "text": "and how founding it was made possible thanks"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 26711.0,
      "end_time": 28694.0,
      "text": "to three very different people"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 28694.0,
      "end_time": 30350.0,
      "text": "with very different talents."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 30360.0,
      "end_time": 31371.0,
      "text": "(popping)"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 31371.0,
      "end_time": 34704.0,
      "text": "(rhythmic techno music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 38522.0,
      "end_time": 40232.0,
      "text": "The story of how Pixar came to be"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 40232.0,
      "end_time": 42457.0,
      "text": "revolves around three major players,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 42457.0,
      "end_time": 43424.0,
      "text": "an artist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 43424.0,
      "end_time": 44722.0,
      "text": "a scientist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 44722.0,
      "end_time": 46103.0,
      "text": "and a businessman."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 46103.0,
      "end_time": 48321.0,
      "text": "All three working together yet separately"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 48321.0,
      "end_time": 52160.0,
      "text": "to one day find each other and create something amazing."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 52170.0,
      "end_time": 53410.0,
      "text": "The artist of this story is a guy"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 53410.0,
      "end_time": 54928.0,
      "text": "named John Lasseter."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 54929.0,
      "end_time": 56308.0,
      "text": "You've probably heard that name."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 56308.0,
      "end_time": 58703.0,
      "text": "John would become an Academy Award winning director"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 58703.0,
      "end_time": 60810.0,
      "text": "responsible for some of Pixar's greatest films"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 60810.0,
      "end_time": 62370.0,
      "text": "including Toy Story."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 62370.0,
      "end_time": 64607.0,
      "text": "But back in 1975 he was a freshman"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 64607.0,
      "end_time": 66859.0,
      "text": "at a brand new program at CalArts"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 66859.0,
      "end_time": 69420.0,
      "text": "learning Disney style animation."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 69430.0,
      "end_time": 70905.0,
      "text": "The program was taught by industry legends"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 70905.0,
      "end_time": 73426.0,
      "text": "including some of Disney's Nine Old Men."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 73426.0,
      "end_time": 76910.0,
      "text": "His classmates included Tim Burton and Brad Bird"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 76910.0,
      "end_time": 78851.0,
      "text": "who would later become prolific filmmakers themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 78851.0,
      "end_time": 81400.0,
      "text": "This was a very exciting and creative environment"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 81400.0,
      "end_time": 82737.0,
      "text": "for an animation student."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 82737.0,
      "end_time": 84770.0,
      "text": "During his time at CalArts John created"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 84770.0,
      "end_time": 87167.0,
      "text": "two student Academy Award winning films"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 87167.0,
      "end_time": 89882.0,
      "text": "and after graduation he got his dream job,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 89882.0,
      "end_time": 93317.0,
      "text": "he was hired by the Walt Disney Animation Studios."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 93317.0,
      "end_time": 94276.0,
      "text": "(dramatic music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 94276.0,
      "end_time": 96996.0,
      "text": "During his time at Disney working as an animator"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 96996.0,
      "end_time": 99463.0,
      "text": "he stumbled upon computer animation."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 99463.0,
      "end_time": 101643.0,
      "text": "He had an idea for making an animated film"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 101643.0,
      "end_time": 103667.0,
      "text": "using computer graphics for the environment"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 103667.0,
      "end_time": 105774.0,
      "text": "and pencil animation for the characters."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 105774.0,
      "end_time": 108400.0,
      "text": "He pitched that idea to Disney executives"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 108400.0,
      "end_time": 108959.0,
      "text": "and they told him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 108959.0,
      "end_time": 110327.0,
      "text": "\"The only reason we would consider"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 110327.0,
      "end_time": 112125.0,
      "text": "\"using computer for animation"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 112125.0,
      "end_time": 114822.0,
      "text": "\"is if it will make it faster or cheaper.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 114822.0,
      "end_time": 118989.0,
      "text": "Shortly after that pitch John was fired from the studio."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 120389.0,
      "end_time": 122164.0,
      "text": "At about the same time George Lucas"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 122165.0,
      "end_time": 124246.0,
      "text": "hired a guy named Ed Catmull"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 124246.0,
      "end_time": 125868.0,
      "text": "to develop a film editing system"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 125868.0,
      "end_time": 127955.0,
      "text": "and digital sound editing system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 127955.0,
      "end_time": 129661.0,
      "text": "all to advance the computer graphics"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 129661.0,
      "end_time": 132744.0,
      "text": "and create ground breaking visual effects for his films."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 132744.0,
      "end_time": 134976.0,
      "text": "Ed Catmull grew up loving animation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 134976.0,
      "end_time": 136857.0,
      "text": "watching cartoons and all Disney films"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 136857.0,
      "end_time": 138389.0,
      "text": "his entire childhood."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 138389.0,
      "end_time": 140271.0,
      "text": "He gave up his dream of becoming an animator,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 140271.0,
      "end_time": 141743.0,
      "text": "thinking he wasn't good enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 141743.0,
      "end_time": 143471.0,
      "text": "and pursued a career in science."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 143471.0,
      "end_time": 146323.0,
      "text": "He studied computer science in the University of Utah"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 146323.0,
      "end_time": 148910.0,
      "text": "where he earned his doctorate and has made"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 148910.0,
      "end_time": 151250.0,
      "text": "ground breaking work in the field of computer imagery."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 151250.0,
      "end_time": 153572.0,
      "text": "He was then asked to run the computer graphics lab"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 153572.0,
      "end_time": 155836.0,
      "text": "in the New York Institute of technology."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 155836.0,
      "end_time": 158230.0,
      "text": "Ed was a brilliant scientist responsible for some"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 158230.0,
      "end_time": 161220.0,
      "text": "of the most commonly used principles of computer animation"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 161220.0,
      "end_time": 162540.0,
      "text": "such as Z-buffer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 162550.0,
      "end_time": 162979.0,
      "text": "texture mapping,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 162979.0,
      "end_time": 164633.0,
      "text": "and subdivision surfaces."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 164633.0,
      "end_time": 167633.0,
      "text": "He basically invented 3D graphics as we know it."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 167633.0,
      "end_time": 169820.0,
      "text": "While working at Lucas Films"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 169820.0,
      "end_time": 170917.0,
      "text": "Ed asked John to join his division"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 170917.0,
      "end_time": 172816.0,
      "text": "after meeting him at an industry event."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 172816.0,
      "end_time": 174391.0,
      "text": "Nothing having the same dream of one day"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 174391.0,
      "end_time": 176982.0,
      "text": "making the first computer animated feature film."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 176982.0,
      "end_time": 178519.0,
      "text": "The two hit it off right away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 178519.0,
      "end_time": 179448.0,
      "text": "but at that time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 179448.0,
      "end_time": 180499.0,
      "text": "1983,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 180499.0,
      "end_time": 182118.0,
      "text": "that dream was still far away."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 182118.0,
      "end_time": 184331.0,
      "text": "(lighthearted music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 184331.0,
      "end_time": 185815.0,
      "text": "That division in Lucas Films,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 185815.0,
      "end_time": 188350.0,
      "text": "then called the Computer Graphics Division,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 188350.0,
      "end_time": 189841.0,
      "text": "produced some of the most revolutionary"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 189841.0,
      "end_time": 192747.0,
      "text": "uses of computer imagery in films for that time."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 192747.0,
      "end_time": 195580.0,
      "text": "They produced the first completely computer generated"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 195580.0,
      "end_time": 197347.0,
      "text": "scene in Star Trek Wrath of Khan"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 197348.0,
      "end_time": 199260.0,
      "text": "and the first computer generated character"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 199260.0,
      "end_time": 201159.0,
      "text": "for Young Sherlock Holmes."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 201159.0,
      "end_time": 203771.0,
      "text": "Within that small division John made the world's"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 203771.0,
      "end_time": 207890.0,
      "text": "first animated short film using computer animation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 207900.0,
      "end_time": 209789.0,
      "text": "The Adventures of Andre and Wally B."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 209789.0,
      "end_time": 212201.0,
      "text": "Creating such complex imagery required building"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 212201.0,
      "end_time": 214420.0,
      "text": "a powerful custom made computer."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 214420.0,
      "end_time": 217554.0,
      "text": "That computer was called the Pixar Image Computer."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 217555.0,
      "end_time": 219703.0,
      "text": "Because of the high demand for computer imagery"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 219703.0,
      "end_time": 222145.0,
      "text": "and advanced computer graphics in other industries"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 222145.0,
      "end_time": 226114.0,
      "text": "the computer graphics division was reimagined as Pixar."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 226114.0,
      "end_time": 228100.0,
      "text": "Still dreaming on making a computer animated"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 228100.0,
      "end_time": 229195.0,
      "text": "full length feature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 229195.0,
      "end_time": 231525.0,
      "text": "a dream George Lucas had no interest in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 231525.0,
      "end_time": 233178.0,
      "text": "Ed looked for an investor to find"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 233178.0,
      "end_time": 234774.0,
      "text": "such a huge undertaking."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 234774.0,
      "end_time": 238191.0,
      "text": "But for a long time there were no takers."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 239593.0,
      "end_time": 241880.0,
      "text": "Meanwhile at Cupertino,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 241880.0,
      "end_time": 243549.0,
      "text": "Steve Jobs who was recently fired from Apple"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 243549.0,
      "end_time": 245846.0,
      "text": "founded his next company called,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 245846.0,
      "end_time": 247261.0,
      "text": "well, NeXT."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 247261.0,
      "end_time": 249268.0,
      "text": "Steve was one of the prospect investors"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 249268.0,
      "end_time": 250925.0,
      "text": "called to take a look at Pixar"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 250925.0,
      "end_time": 252392.0,
      "text": "and he decided to invest."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 252392.0,
      "end_time": 255433.0,
      "text": "He bought Pixar from George Lucas for five million dollars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 255433.0,
      "end_time": 256962.0,
      "text": "throwing an additional five million"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 256963.00000000003,
      "end_time": 258634.00000000003,
      "text": "to keep the company running."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 258634.0,
      "end_time": 260551.0,
      "text": "After the acquisition the team wanted"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 260551.0,
      "end_time": 263606.0,
      "text": "to make another animated short to establish who they were"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 263606.0,
      "end_time": 265791.0,
      "text": "and stay on the track of filmmaking."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 265791.0,
      "end_time": 268673.0,
      "text": "John, who loved animating inanimate objects,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 268673.0,
      "end_time": 270842.0,
      "text": "single handedly animated a short film"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 270842.0,
      "end_time": 273518.0,
      "text": "about a lamp and it's offspring titled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 273518.0,
      "end_time": 274952.0,
      "text": "Luxo Junior."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 274952.0,
      "end_time": 276573.0,
      "text": "That short film was later nominated"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 276573.0,
      "end_time": 278469.0,
      "text": "for an Academy Award and was the first"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 278469.0,
      "end_time": 281732.0,
      "text": "computer generated short to ever receive that nomination."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 281732.0,
      "end_time": 285899.0,
      "text": "The lamp from that film then became Pixar's mascot."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 287756.0,
      "end_time": 289635.0,
      "text": "Despite the massive potential though,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 289635.0,
      "end_time": 291255.0,
      "text": "Pixar was still struggling."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 291255.0,
      "end_time": 293329.0,
      "text": "They were licensing their rendering software."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 293329.0,
      "end_time": 294315.0,
      "text": "RenderMan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 294315.0,
      "end_time": 295880.0,
      "text": "which became the industry standard"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 295880.0,
      "end_time": 298344.0,
      "text": "for visual effects in films used in major pictures"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 298345.0,
      "end_time": 300120.0,
      "text": "such as Jurassic Park."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 300120.0,
      "end_time": 302706.0,
      "text": "But despite that they still couldn't turn a profit."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 302706.0,
      "end_time": 304350.0,
      "text": "They started doing commercials,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 304350.0,
      "end_time": 307620.0,
      "text": "getting clients like Trident and Tropicana."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 307620.0,
      "end_time": 308780.0,
      "text": "They did medical visualization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 308780.0,
      "end_time": 309808.0,
      "text": "seismic imaging,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 309808.0,
      "end_time": 311413.0,
      "text": "they sold their hardware,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 311413.0,
      "end_time": 314254.0,
      "text": "the Pixar Image Computer, which was very expensive."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 314254.0,
      "end_time": 316160.0,
      "text": "Yet with all their effort they couldn't make"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 316160.0,
      "end_time": 318483.0,
      "text": "their product commercially viable enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 318483.0,
      "end_time": 320100.0,
      "text": "to sustain themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 320100.0,
      "end_time": 322248.0,
      "text": "Steve Jobs was losing about one million dollars"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 322248.0,
      "end_time": 324906.0,
      "text": "every year for five years."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 324906.0,
      "end_time": 326936.0,
      "text": "The dire financial problems didn't stop the team"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 326936.0,
      "end_time": 329298.0,
      "text": "from making more computer animated shorts."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 329298.0,
      "end_time": 330284.0,
      "text": "Their third film,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 330284.0,
      "end_time": 331117.0,
      "text": "Tin Toy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 331117.0,
      "end_time": 332949.0,
      "text": "telling the story of toys trying to escape"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 332949.0,
      "end_time": 336685.0,
      "text": "a terrifying baby won the Academy Award in 1988."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 336685.0,
      "end_time": 339582.0,
      "text": "Disney, who not that long ago before had fired John,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 339582.0,
      "end_time": 342140.0,
      "text": "saw the success of his shorts and asked him to come back"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 342140.0,
      "end_time": 344185.0,
      "text": "and direct a feature film for them."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 344185.0,
      "end_time": 346200.0,
      "text": "This was a life long dream for John"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 346200.0,
      "end_time": 347945.0,
      "text": "and he was currently working on a company"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 347946.0,
      "end_time": 349639.0,
      "text": "on the brink of bankruptcy."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 349639.0,
      "end_time": 351760.0,
      "text": "Yet he refused Disney"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 351760.0,
      "end_time": 352510.0,
      "text": "and he stayed with Pixar"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 352510.0,
      "end_time": 354390.0,
      "text": "still dreaming to make the first"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 354400.0,
      "end_time": 356209.0,
      "text": "computer animated feature film."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 356209.0,
      "end_time": 358876.0,
      "text": "(subdued music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 362167.0,
      "end_time": 363765.0,
      "text": "After the success of Tin Toy"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 363765.0,
      "end_time": 366252.0,
      "text": "the idea of an entire film from the toy's point of view"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 366252.0,
      "end_time": 367337.0,
      "text": "stuck with them."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 367337.0,
      "end_time": 370900.0,
      "text": "And despite refusing Disney not too long beforehand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 370900.0,
      "end_time": 372792.0,
      "text": "he knew that if he wanted to make a fully length film"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 372792.0,
      "end_time": 375128.0,
      "text": "they would need the financial support of a larger studio"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 375128.0,
      "end_time": 376792.0,
      "text": "for marketing and distribution."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 376792.0,
      "end_time": 378546.0,
      "text": "Disney was the perfect candidate."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 378547.0,
      "end_time": 381355.0,
      "text": "He pitched them the idea and they loved it."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 381355.0,
      "end_time": 384960.0,
      "text": "At that time animated feature had only one style,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 384960.0,
      "end_time": 385472.0,
      "text": "the Disney style."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 385472.0,
      "end_time": 388116.0,
      "text": "That style was so established that when Tom Hanks"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 388116.0,
      "end_time": 390654.0,
      "text": "was asked to do the voice for the film he asked,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 390654.0,
      "end_time": 392728.0,
      "text": "\"You're not gonna make me sing, are ya?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 392728.0,
      "end_time": 395309.0,
      "text": "But the people at Pixar wanted to do it differently."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 395309.0,
      "end_time": 397766.0,
      "text": "They had a set of rules they set for themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 397766.0,
      "end_time": 398892.0,
      "text": "There would be no songs."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 398892.0,
      "end_time": 403780.0,
      "text": "♫ Mister I'll make a man"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 403780.0,
      "end_time": 404808.0,
      "text": "♫ Out of you ♫"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 404809.0,
      "end_time": 406653.0,
      "text": "No \"I want\" moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 406653.0,
      "end_time": 410400.0,
      "text": "♫ I want to be where the people are ♫"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 410400.0,
      "end_time": 411250.0,
      "text": "No happy village."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 411250.0,
      "end_time": 412830.0,
      "text": "♫ Bojour"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 412830.0,
      "end_time": 412916.0,
      "text": "♫ Bojour"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 412916.0,
      "end_time": 414928.0,
      "text": "♫ Bojour, Bojour, Bojour ♫"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 414928.0,
      "end_time": 416142.0,
      "text": "No love story."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 416142.0,
      "end_time": 419974.0,
      "text": "♫ Can you feel the love ♫"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 419974.0,
      "end_time": 421541.0,
      "text": "And no villain."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 421541.0,
      "end_time": 423870.0,
      "text": "This went against everything that was"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 423870.0,
      "end_time": 426589.0,
      "text": "proving to be working in the animation industry at the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 426589.0,
      "end_time": 428837.0,
      "text": "Despite their drive to do something different"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 428837.0,
      "end_time": 430623.0,
      "text": "Disney executives were at their backs"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 430623.0,
      "end_time": 432638.0,
      "text": "giving them notes and ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 432638.0,
      "end_time": 434118.0,
      "text": "They were the experienced studio,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 434118.0,
      "end_time": 436963.0,
      "text": "they though they knew what makes animated films work."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 436963.0,
      "end_time": 438633.0,
      "text": "After a year of preparation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 438633.0,
      "end_time": 441164.0,
      "text": "working on story boards and story reels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 441164.0,
      "end_time": 443510.0,
      "text": "guided by Disney they screened the pitch"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 443511.0,
      "end_time": 445979.0,
      "text": "of what would later become Toy Story."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 445979.0,
      "end_time": 447580.0,
      "text": "Disney hated it."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 447580.0,
      "end_time": 448611.0,
      "text": "It wasn't funny,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 448612.0,
      "end_time": 449899.0,
      "text": "it wasn't moving,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 449899.0,
      "end_time": 451694.0,
      "text": "Woody was a horrible character."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 451694.0,
      "end_time": 453980.0,
      "text": "The film was clearly not working,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 453980.0,
      "end_time": 456203.0,
      "text": "Disney shut down production the next day."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 456203.0,
      "end_time": 459681.0,
      "text": "(lighthearted music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 459681.0,
      "end_time": 461534.0,
      "text": "This could have been the end for Pixar."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 461534.0,
      "end_time": 462962.0,
      "text": "However, John did not give up"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 462962.0,
      "end_time": 464777.0,
      "text": "on the story he believed in."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 464778.0,
      "end_time": 466539.0,
      "text": "Within a period of three weeks"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 466539.0,
      "end_time": 468811.0,
      "text": "with a talented yet small team"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 468811.0,
      "end_time": 472400.0,
      "text": "he completely re-did the story like originally he wanted to"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 472400.0,
      "end_time": 473791.0,
      "text": "without all the notes and ideas"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 473791.0,
      "end_time": 476101.0,
      "text": "from experienced Disney executives."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 476101.0,
      "end_time": 477474.0,
      "text": "They had a second screening"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 477474.0,
      "end_time": 479484.0,
      "text": "and this time the story worked,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 479484.0,
      "end_time": 481753.0,
      "text": "production was back on track."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 481753.0,
      "end_time": 484306.0,
      "text": "The film took almost five years to make,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 484307.0,
      "end_time": 486519.0,
      "text": "and in 1995 it was released to become"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 486519.0,
      "end_time": 488890.0,
      "text": "the highest grossing film of that year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 488890.0,
      "end_time": 491839.0,
      "text": "making 192 million dollars domestically"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 491839.0,
      "end_time": 495153.0,
      "text": "and 362 million dollars worldwide."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 495153.0,
      "end_time": 497303.0,
      "text": "The film got three Oscar nominations"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 497303.0,
      "end_time": 499269.0,
      "text": "and John received a special achievement award"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 499269.0,
      "end_time": 502587.0,
      "text": "for making the first computer animated feature film."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 502587.0,
      "end_time": 504539.0,
      "text": "It seemed that Pixar was is the clear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 504539.0,
      "end_time": 507615.0,
      "text": "the studio was now a success and their worries were over."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 507615.0,
      "end_time": 509500.0,
      "text": "But that was not the case."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 509500.0,
      "end_time": 511203.0,
      "text": "There was one big problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 511203.0,
      "end_time": 513256.0,
      "text": "According to the deal they made with Disney"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 513256.0,
      "end_time": 515525.0,
      "text": "Pixar didn't have the rights to any of the profits"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 515525.0,
      "end_time": 516756.0,
      "text": "for merchandise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 516756.0,
      "end_time": 519382.0,
      "text": "and in fact barely made any money from the film."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 519383.00000000006,
      "end_time": 521746.00000000006,
      "text": "They were still struggling financially."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 521746.0,
      "end_time": 524384.0,
      "text": "They decided that their only choice was to go public"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 524384.0,
      "end_time": 526690.0,
      "text": "in order to raise capital."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 526690.0,
      "end_time": 529299.0,
      "text": "They went on to be the biggest IPO of 1995,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 529299.0,
      "end_time": 530937.0,
      "text": "exceeding even Netscape,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 530937.0,
      "end_time": 533803.0,
      "text": "raising 132 million dollars."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 533803.0,
      "end_time": 535100.0,
      "text": "(gentle music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 535100.0,
      "end_time": 536626.0,
      "text": "Disney wanted to renew their agreement"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 536626.0,
      "end_time": 538482.0,
      "text": "to distribute more Pixar films,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 538482.0,
      "end_time": 540225.0,
      "text": "and they signed a new contract to produce"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 540225.0,
      "end_time": 543427.0,
      "text": "five more films together over the period of 10 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 543427.0,
      "end_time": 546497.0,
      "text": "this time dividing the profits 50/50."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 546497.0,
      "end_time": 547717.0,
      "text": "Pixar was still, however,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 547717.0,
      "end_time": 549851.0,
      "text": "a single success story so far,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 549851.0,
      "end_time": 552200.0,
      "text": "not sure if Toy Story was just a fluke."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 552200.0,
      "end_time": 553636.0,
      "text": "So it was their second film that would"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 553636.0,
      "end_time": 555704.0,
      "text": "determine the future of the studio."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 555704.0,
      "end_time": 558123.0,
      "text": "Luckily A Bug's Life would become the most successful"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 558124.0,
      "end_time": 560445.0,
      "text": "animated film of that year."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 560445.0,
      "end_time": 562236.0,
      "text": "The studio started growing rapidly"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 562236.0,
      "end_time": 563934.0,
      "text": "and their headquarters became too small"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 563934.0,
      "end_time": 565764.0,
      "text": "to host the number of people in it."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 565764.0,
      "end_time": 568400.0,
      "text": "Steve had his eyes on a huge lot in Emeryville"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 568400.0,
      "end_time": 570887.0,
      "text": "and there he designed the new Pixar headquarters"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 570887.0,
      "end_time": 572838.0,
      "text": "based around the idea of open space"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 572838.0,
      "end_time": 574653.0,
      "text": "and unplanned collaboration."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 574653.0,
      "end_time": 576846.0,
      "text": "A huge space where people from different departments"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 576846.0,
      "end_time": 579121.0,
      "text": "can run into each other instead of being segregated"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 579121.0,
      "end_time": 581326.0,
      "text": "in small rooms on different floors."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 581326.0,
      "end_time": 583725.0,
      "text": "And then finally in 2000 the Pixar team"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 583725.0,
      "end_time": 585547.0,
      "text": "had moved to it's new location"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 585547.0,
      "end_time": 587367.0,
      "text": "and stayed there ever since."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 587367.0,
      "end_time": 589331.0,
      "text": "The proceeded to break their own records"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 589331.0,
      "end_time": 590659.0,
      "text": "time and time again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 590659.0,
      "end_time": 591911.0,
      "text": "making some of the most successful"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 591911.0,
      "end_time": 593593.0,
      "text": "animated films in history."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 593594.0,
      "end_time": 595471.0,
      "text": "But troubles were still to come,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 595471.0,
      "end_time": 597295.0,
      "text": "the contract with Disney was up"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 597295.0,
      "end_time": 599990.0,
      "text": "and their relationship went sour."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 599100.0,
      "end_time": 601391.0,
      "text": "That could have been the end for their collaboration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 601391.0,
      "end_time": 603623.0,
      "text": "but Disney had the rights to keep making sequels"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 603624.0,
      "end_time": 605643.0,
      "text": "to Pixar films if they wanted to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 605643.0,
      "end_time": 607614.0,
      "text": "and John couldn't bear the thought of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 607614.0,
      "end_time": 608647.0,
      "text": "It was like having your kids"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 608647.0,
      "end_time": 610598.0,
      "text": "begin raised by someone else."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 610598.0,
      "end_time": 612545.0,
      "text": "Luckily for everyone Disney went through"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 612545.0,
      "end_time": 614613.0,
      "text": "a much needed change of leadership"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 614614.0,
      "end_time": 616814.0,
      "text": "and Bob Iger took over as president."
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 616814.0,
      "end_time": 618678.0,
      "text": "With the goal of reviving the Disney studio"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 618678.0,
      "end_time": 620130.0,
      "text": "back to it's glory days,"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 620130.0,
      "end_time": 621640.0,
      "text": "on his first week as president"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 621640.0,
      "end_time": 623449.0,
      "text": "Bob called Steve for a meeting."
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 623450.0,
      "end_time": 625811.0,
      "text": "He wanted to merge the two companies together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 625811.0,
      "end_time": 628878.0,
      "text": "feeling that Pixar knew something that Disney had forgotten."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 628878.0,
      "end_time": 630179.0,
      "text": "This seemed like a horrible thought"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 630179.0,
      "end_time": 631728.0,
      "text": "to the people working at Pixar"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 631728.0,
      "end_time": 633846.0,
      "text": "after their negative experience with Disney,"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 633846.0,
      "end_time": 636598.0,
      "text": "and the fear of losing their identity was great."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 636598.0,
      "end_time": 638800.0,
      "text": "But Steve felt that Bob was different"
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 638801.0,
      "end_time": 640206.0,
      "text": "and had the right idea for the future"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 640206.0,
      "end_time": 641769.0,
      "text": "of the two companies."
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 641769.0,
      "end_time": 644213.0,
      "text": "They worked hard for a long time on a contract"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 644213.0,
      "end_time": 646838.0,
      "text": "and in 2006 Disney bought Pixar"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 646838.0,
      "end_time": 649276.0,
      "text": "for 7.4 billion dollars."
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 649276.0,
      "end_time": 652757.0,
      "text": "That deal made Steve Jobs the largest shareholder at Disney,"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 652757.0,
      "end_time": 654512.0,
      "text": "John Lasetter the chief creative officer"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 654513.0,
      "end_time": 656612.0,
      "text": "of both Disney and Pixar,"
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 656612.0,
      "end_time": 659314.0,
      "text": "including overseeing all of Disney's theme parks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 659315.0,
      "end_time": 661407.0,
      "text": "and Ed Catmull the president of Pixar"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 661407.0,
      "end_time": 663824.0,
      "text": "and Disney animation studios."
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 664901.0,
      "end_time": 666329.0,
      "text": "(gentle music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 666329.0,
      "end_time": 669820.0,
      "text": "The studio went on to keep producing hit after hit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 669820.0,
      "end_time": 670914.0,
      "text": "winning multiple Academy Awards."
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 670914.0,
      "end_time": 674209.0,
      "text": "And in 2010 Toy Story 3 became the highest grossing"
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 674209.0,
      "end_time": 676113.0,
      "text": "animated film of all time."
    },
    {
      "index": 317,
      "start_time": 676114.0,
      "end_time": 677615.0,
      "text": "After years of struggle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 318,
      "start_time": 677615.0,
      "end_time": 678448.0,
      "text": "uncertainty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 319,
      "start_time": 678448.0,
      "end_time": 680286.0,
      "text": "and living in fear of shutting down"
    },
    {
      "index": 320,
      "start_time": 680286.0,
      "end_time": 681637.0,
      "text": "Pixar had made it"
    },
    {
      "index": 321,
      "start_time": 681638.0,
      "end_time": 684884.0,
      "text": "all thanks to the devotion and talent of one artist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 322,
      "start_time": 684884.0,
      "end_time": 686287.0,
      "text": "one scientist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 323,
      "start_time": 686287.0,
      "end_time": 688306.0,
      "text": "and one businessman."
    },
    {
      "index": 324,
      "start_time": 688306.0,
      "end_time": 689973.0,
      "text": "Thanks for watching."
    }
  ]
}